# Swift / AppKit

## Conventions

- Match existing naming and file placement (`Services/` for gateway/config logic; top-level for app shell).
- Cross-feature coordination via `NotificationCenter` (e.g. `CodexGatewayStatusChanged`, `CodexGatewayUpdateAvailable`).
- Prefer extending existing types over new abstractions for one-off logic.

## App shell

- Menu bar only: `NSApplication.setActivationPolicy(.accessory)` in `main.swift`.
- `StatusBarController` — menu bar icon via `CodexBrandIcon.mark()` with status dot fallback.
- `AppDelegate` — starts/stops `GatewayServer`, wires health polling.

## Avoid

- Large refactors unrelated to the task.
- Blocking the main thread for network calls — use `URLSession` async APIs.
- Finishing with code-only diffs — update `ARCHITECTURE.md`, tests, and user docs per `docs-and-tests.mdc`.
